ENUGU – There was pandemonium in Enugu on Monday following rumoured gun shots in different locations in the metropolis by unknown gunmen. Our Correspondent gathered that people started running heater skelter on Monday morning in different locations which include, Amechi Akwakunanaw, Holy Ghost market, Okpara Avenue, Trans Ekulu, Abakpa, Nike road among others. We’re Ready To Dwarf Activities Of Miscreants Enforcing… FRSC Condemns Recycled Old Video Of Encounter With Tricycle… An eye witness account, Chiedozie Nnnaji told our correspondent that some suspected members of IPOB engaged in a shooting spree in Amechi Akwananaw community on Monday morning an act meant to attack people for disobeying IPOB sit at home which was earlier cancelled Nnaji said a commercial bus and tricycle were set ablaze in the area while people ran back home for safety “it’s unfortunate that we are still experiencing this ugly act this new year. The Sit at home was cancelled last year and things became normal in Enugu, why this crisis again,” he asked The rumour of the attack which spread to other parts of the city causes tension forcing residents to run for safety Our correspondent reports that traders at the popular holy ghost market as well as other parts of the city hurriedly locked up their shops while banks and offices opened earlier in the day also closed down A resident of Maryland, Grace Ogbe told our correspondent that she tracked from her office for over 1 hour before she could get the tricycle that brought her home, POLL “I went to work this morning at Trans Ekulu but around 10 am, we saw people running helter-skelter and we were asked to go home because gunmen were shooting around liberty area in Abakpa but we are yet to confirm if it was IPOB or any other group When contacted, the police spokesperson of Enugu state command Daniel Ndukwe said “I will get back to you when I get relevant information.